verses.text_plain: Hear my prayer, O Lord, and let my cry come unto thee.
verses.verse_html:
1Hear my prayer, O Lord, and let my cry come unto thee. ▼
▼ of: or, for

verses.text_plain: Hide not thy face from me in the day when I am in trouble; incline thine ear unto me: in the day when I call answer me speedily.
verses.verse_html: 2Hide not thy face from me in the day when I am in trouble; incline thine ear unto me: in the day when I call answer me speedily.

verses.text_plain: For my days are consumed like smoke, and my bones are burned as an hearth.
verses.verse_html:
3For my days are consumed like smoke, and my bones are burned as an hearth. ▼
▼ like…: or, (as some read) into smoke

footnotes.body_text: ▼ like…: or, (as some read) into smoke
footnotes.body_html: ▼ like…: or, (as some read) into smoke

verses.text_plain: My heart is smitten, and withered like grass; so that I forget to eat my bread.
verses.verse_html: 4My heart is smitten, and withered like grass; so that I forget to eat my bread.

verses.text_plain: By reason of the voice of my groaning my bones cleave to my skin.
verses.verse_html:
5By reason of the voice of my groaning my bones cleave to my skin. ▼
▼ skin: or, flesh

verses.text_plain: I am like a pelican of the wilderness: I am like an owl of the desert.
verses.verse_html: 6I am like a pelican of the wilderness: I am like an owl of the desert.

verses.text_plain: I watch, and am as a sparrow alone upon the house top.
verses.verse_html: 7I watch, and am as a sparrow alone upon the house top.

verses.text_plain: Mine enemies reproach me all the day; and they that are mad against me are sworn against me.
verses.verse_html: 8Mine enemies reproach me all the day; and they that are mad against me are sworn against me.

verses.text_plain: For I have eaten ashes like bread, and mingled my drink with weeping,
verses.verse_html: 9For I have eaten ashes like bread, and mingled my drink with weeping,

verses.text_plain: Because of thine indignation and thy wrath: for thou hast lifted me up, and cast me down.
verses.verse_html: 10Because of thine indignation and thy wrath: for thou hast lifted me up, and cast me down.

tokens.text: for thou hast lifted me up

verses.text_plain: My days are like a shadow that declineth; and I am withered like grass.
verses.verse_html: 11My days are like a shadow that declineth; and I am withered like grass.

verses.text_plain: But thou, O Lord, shalt endure for ever; and thy remembrance unto all generations.
verses.verse_html: 12But thou, O Lord, shalt endure for ever; and thy remembrance unto all generations.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt arise, and have mercy upon Zion: for the time to favour her, yea, the set time, is come.
verses.verse_html: 13Thou shalt arise, and have mercy upon Zion: for the time to favour her, yea, the set time, is come.

verses.text_plain: For thy servants take pleasure in her stones, and favour the dust thereof.
verses.verse_html: 14For thy servants take pleasure in her stones, and favour the dust thereof.

verses.text_plain: So the heathen shall fear the name of the Lord, and all the kings of the earth thy glory.
verses.verse_html: 15So the heathen shall fear the name of the Lord, and all the kings of the earth thy glory.

verses.text_plain: When the Lord shall build up Zion, he shall appear in his glory.
verses.verse_html: 16When the Lord shall build up Zion, he shall appear in his glory.

verses.text_plain: He will regard the prayer of the destitute, and not despise their prayer.
verses.verse_html: 17He will regard the prayer of the destitute, and not despise their prayer.

verses.text_plain: This shall be written for the generation to come: and the people which shall be created shall praise the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 18This shall be written for the generation to come: and the people which shall be created shall praise the Lord.

verses.text_plain: For he hath looked down from the height of his sanctuary; from heaven did the Lord behold the earth;
verses.verse_html: 19For he hath looked down from the height of his sanctuary; from heaven did the Lord behold the earth;

verses.text_plain: To hear the groaning of the prisoner; to loose those that are appointed to death;
verses.verse_html:
20To hear the groaning of the prisoner; to loose those that are appointed to death; ▼
▼ those…: Heb. the children of death

footnotes.body_text: ▼ those…: Heb. the children of death
footnotes.body_html: ▼ those…: Heb. the children of death

verses.text_plain: To declare the name of the Lord in Zion, and his praise in Jerusalem;
verses.verse_html: 21To declare the name of the Lord in Zion, and his praise in Jerusalem;

verses.text_plain: When the people are gathered together, and the kingdoms, to serve the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 22When the people are gathered together, and the kingdoms, to serve the Lord.

verses.text_plain: He weakened my strength in the way; he shortened my days.
verses.verse_html:
23He weakened my strength in the way; he shortened my days. ▼
▼ weakened: Heb. afflicted

verses.text_plain: I said, O my God, take me not away in the midst of my days: thy years are throughout all generations.
verses.verse_html: 24I said, O my God, take me not away in the midst of my days: thy years are throughout all generations.

verses.text_plain: Of old hast thou laid the foundation of the earth: and the heavens are the work of thy hands.
verses.verse_html: 25Of old hast thou laid the foundation of the earth: and the heavens are the work of thy hands.

verses.text_plain: They shall perish, but thou shalt endure: yea, all of them shall wax old like a garment; as a vesture shalt thou change them, and they shall be changed:
verses.verse_html:
26They shall perish, but thou shalt endure: yea, all of them shall wax old like a garment; as a vesture shalt thou change them, and they shall be changed: ▼
▼ endure: Heb. stand

tokens.text: yea, all of them shall wax old
them, and they shall be changed

verses.text_plain: But thou art the same, and thy years shall have no end.
verses.verse_html: 27But thou art the same, and thy years shall have no end.

verses.text_plain: The children of thy servants shall continue, and their seed shall be established before thee.
verses.verse_html: 28The children of thy servants shall continue, and their seed shall be established before thee.
